Apavil SA, a Romanian utility, is
seeking bids for water-treatment plant improvements in the
southern county of Valcea under a contract valued at 28.6
million lei ($8 million).  Bidders may apply by Aug. 14 for the 28-month contract,
which includes upgrades to plants in the towns of Dragasani,
Olanesti and Valea lui Stan, according to a  procurement notice 
published today on the European Unionâ€™s tender website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
